00:00:53,253 --> 00:00:54,987
narrator: the bead is the lip of the tire              

4
00:00:54,989 --> 00:00:57,856
that fits to a wheel rim.    

5
00:00:57,858 --> 00:01:00,192
high-tensile steel wires inside the bead         

6
00:01:00,194 --> 00:01:05,731
pull the tire tightly and uniformly to the rim.    

7
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:08,267
these bead wires provide stability        

8
00:01:08,269 --> 00:01:10,536
so the wheels can start turning.            

9
00:01:14,742 --> 00:01:16,608
these bronze-coated steel wires              

10
00:01:16,610 --> 00:01:19,278
are the muscle in the bead of a tire.      

11
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,879
they're a source of hidden strength        

12
00:01:20,881 --> 00:01:23,015
that we don't usually think about.    

13
00:01:23,017 --> 00:01:26,819
but without them, tires wouldn't properly grip the rim,              

14
00:01:26,821 --> 00:01:29,689
and riding on wheels would be dangerous.       

15
00:01:34,762 --> 00:01:38,764
production starts with coils of high-carbon steel.      

16
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:43,568
a forklift slides the coils onto metal cones.        

17
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:47,773
a worker cuts the ties around the wire.         

18
00:01:47,775 --> 00:01:49,842
then the cone moves into an upright position     

19
00:01:49,844 --> 00:01:52,110
on the carousel.         

20
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,646
a motorized system        

21
00:01:53,648 --> 00:01:56,582
uncoils the wire and pulls it up through the cone.        

22
00:01:59,654 --> 00:02:01,120
at the top,           

23
00:02:01,122 --> 00:02:05,925
a guide positions the wire to enter a descaler.       

24
00:02:05,927 --> 00:02:08,994
the device           
has a revolving sandpaper belt  

25
00:02:08,996 --> 00:02:11,430
which smoothes and refines the wire.            

26
00:02:15,335 --> 00:02:16,936
next, the wire travels      

27
00:02:16,938 --> 00:02:19,071
through a channel filled with powdered soap,    

28
00:02:19,073 --> 00:02:21,674
which acts as a dry lubricant.  

29
00:02:21,676 --> 00:02:26,012
then, the system pulls the wire through a series of dies,    

30
00:02:26,014 --> 00:02:28,748
each with progressively smaller openings.            

31
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,820
the process is called drawing  

32
00:02:34,822 --> 00:02:37,423
because it draws        
down the diameter of the wire,  

33
00:02:37,425 --> 00:02:40,626
stretching it longer and thinner.           

34
00:02:40,628 --> 00:02:44,764
the process reduces the wire's diameter by almost half.     

35
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:48,433
a carriage lifts the thinner wire      

36
00:02:48,435 --> 00:02:50,503
onto a spool that winds it up.  

37
00:02:53,708 --> 00:02:55,708
the table the spool sits on turns          

38
00:02:55,710 --> 00:02:58,377
to deliver the wire to the next operation.      

39
00:03:01,516 --> 00:03:04,049
the spool of wire is one of 40  

40
00:03:04,051 --> 00:03:07,953
that now unwind simultaneously at a controlled speed.      

41
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:14,793
large cones keep them separate  

42
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:16,529
so they'll be ready for the next stage        

43
00:03:16,531 --> 00:03:19,965
of the journey --        

44
00:03:19,967 --> 00:03:22,034
a trip through a long oven.   

45
00:03:28,142 --> 00:03:31,610
it's heated to an incredible 1,800 degrees.            

46
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:36,749
inside, intense heat       

47
00:03:36,751 --> 00:03:39,818
recrystalizes the microstructure of the wires.          

48
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:43,889
this reduces brittleness.    

49
00:03:43,891 --> 00:03:46,292
then spools take up the wires.  

50
00:03:48,429 --> 00:03:50,228
the wires take a dip in a tank  

51
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:53,199
filled with hot water and phosphate solution.     

52
00:03:56,104 --> 00:03:59,872
a floating foam blanket keeps the solution hot.     

53
00:04:01,776 --> 00:04:04,777
the phosphate solution and a subsequent rinse lubricate            

54
00:04:04,779 --> 00:04:07,780
the bead wire for the next process --     

55
00:04:07,782 --> 00:04:09,248
a second drawing         

56
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,951
that squeezes the wire even longer and narrower.    

57
00:04:14,388 --> 00:04:17,989
the holes in a series of dies become progressively narrower  

58
00:04:17,991 --> 00:04:22,394
to reduce the wire's diameter even further.          

59
00:04:22,396 --> 00:04:24,330
after each trip through a die,  

60
00:04:24,332 --> 00:04:26,531
a drum winds up the wire.    

61
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:31,604
each drum turns a little    
faster than the one before it.  

62
00:04:31,606 --> 00:04:33,539
that's because longer wires   

63
00:04:33,541 --> 00:04:36,509
need to be wound up quicker to prevent slack in the system.             

64
00:04:40,414 --> 00:04:42,080
this final drawing process    

65
00:04:42,082 --> 00:04:46,218
brings the wire's diameter down to less than 1 millimeter.           

66
00:04:48,489 --> 00:04:51,390
the bead wires are now at the correct width.  

67
00:04:56,230 --> 00:05:00,766
next, the bead wires receive their bronze coating.  

68
00:05:00,768 --> 00:05:02,234
bronzing the steel wires     

69
00:05:02,236 --> 00:05:05,037
allows them to adhere to the tire rubber.       

70
00:05:07,642 --> 00:05:10,042
after the bronze solution dries,             

71
00:05:10,044 --> 00:05:12,444
two rollers straighten the wires.      

72
00:05:14,782 --> 00:05:18,384
then a spool winds up the bead wire.     

73
00:05:18,386 --> 00:05:20,719
they produce bead wire in different thicknesses     

74
00:05:20,721 --> 00:05:24,256
and metal coatings for a variety of tire sizes.   

75
00:05:27,461 --> 00:05:31,730
they test the wires       
before they leave the factory.  

76
00:05:31,732 --> 00:05:34,466
if it can withstand up to 1,500 pounds of force     

77
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:36,401
before it breaks,        

78
00:05:36,403 --> 00:05:39,171
then it's ready to be shipped to the tire factory.       

79
00:05:41,676 --> 00:05:44,343
once they're installed in rubber tires,         

80
00:05:44,345 --> 00:05:45,810
these bead wires will be     

81
00:05:45,812 --> 00:05:48,681
an important source of strength, doing their part  

82
00:05:48,683 --> 00:05:51,650
to keep your vehicle moving forward safely.      

